# Media from S3 / CloudFront (no trailing slash). When set:
# - `npm run dev` / `npm run build` resolve /media/... URLs to this origin.
# - Pre-scripts skip copying Kruler's Media → public/media (you can remove local public/media).
# Upload the same tree as before to: s3://YOUR_BUCKET/media/  →  then use bucket website URL or CloudFront:
#   VITE_MEDIA_BASE_URL=https://your-distribution.cloudfront.net
# Prefer virtual-hosted URL without a region (avoids 301 / broken <img> if region is wrong):
#   VITE_MEDIA_BASE_URL=https://YOUR_BUCKET.s3.amazonaws.com
# If you use a regional hostname, it must match the bucket’s region (see x-amz-bucket-region on failed requests).
#
# Local-only: leave unset or empty to use `npm run sync-media` + files in public/media.
#
# Vercel: set `VITE_MEDIA_BASE_URL` (Production) to your bucket or CDN origin so client URLs
# resolve correctly. Prebuild skips copying Kruler's Media; without `public/media` in the
# repo, `generate-property-images` keeps the committed `generatedPropertyImages.js`.

# Optional: full HTTPS URL for header/footer logo (default is `public/Navbar-logo.png` → `/Navbar-logo.png`).
# VITE_NAVBAR_LOGO_URL=

VITE_MEDIA_BASE_URL=

# Default: off — site uses your existing S3 files as-is (no re-upload).
# VITE_USE_MEDIA_VARIANTS=true
